      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstration that the selected QoIs (RHI, volume-averaged shear stress, exposure time distribution) are mechanistically linked to pump-induced hemolysis and are sufficient for the regulatory decision.",
      "rationale": "RHI is the primary regulatory metric per FDA guidance on blood pump hemolysis assessment. Volume-averaged shear stress and Lagrangian exposure time distributions are mechanistically linked to red blood cell damage through the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. QoI selection reviewed and approved by clinical advisor. Meets Gradation 2."
    },
    {
